{{Infobox video game |title = John Deere: American Farmer |image = John Deere - American Farmer Coverart.png |caption = Cover art |developer = [[Gabriel Entertainment]] |publisher = [[Destineer|Destineer Studios]] |designer = |series = |engine = |released = {{vgrelease|NA|June 23, 2004<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/computer/doswin/data/921165.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-01-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070318031837/http://www.gamefaqs.com/computer/doswin/data/921165.html |archivedate=2007-03-18 |df= }}</ref>}} |genre = [[construction and management simulation games|Construction and management simulation]] |modes = |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] }}
'''''John Deere: American Farmer''''' is a [[farm]] [[construction and management simulation games|construction and management simulation]] for [[Microsoft Windows]] featuring the [[John Deere]] license, developed by [[Gabriel Entertainment]], published by [[Take 2 Interactive]] and [[Destineer|Destineer Studios]].
The goal of the game is to make a living by raising livestock such as beef cattle, dairy cows, and pigs, or by growing crops such as sunflowers, soybeans, wheat and corn. Players must contend with factors such as weather, market demand, employee skill.
There is a variety of John Deere equipment to choose from such as the 7820, 9520 and 5303 tractors with numerous attachments, and the 9660 combine with a hydraflex and corn headers. There are also smaller vehicles such as the John Deere Gator and ATVs. There is a built-in [[map editor]] that enables players to create their own map.
In 2006 a sequel, ''John Deere: American Farmer Deluxe'' was released and received positive reviews.
