{{Infobox animanga/Header | name = | image = Kosaku Shima.png | caption = ''Kachō Kōsaku Shima'' featured in the cover of ''[[Weekly Morning]]'' | ja_kanji = 課長島耕作 | ja_romaji = Kachō Shima Kōsaku | genre = }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = manga | title = Kōsaku Shima Series | author = [[Kenshi Hirokane]] | publisher = [[Kodansha]] | demographic = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]'' | magazine = [[Weekly Morning]] | first = 1983 | last = | volumes = 75 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = manga | title = Kōsaku Shima Spin-off Series | author = Kenshi Hirokane | publisher = Kodansha | demographic = ''Seinen'' | magazine = [[Evening (magazine)|Evening]] | first = 2001 | last = | volumes = 22 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Footer}}
{{nihongo|'''''Kachō Kōsaku Shima'''''|課長島耕作|lead=yes}} is the first in a number of [[Japan]]ese [[manga]] series, by [[Kenshi Hirokane]], about a fictional [[salaryman]] named Kōsaku Shima. The series ran from 1983–1992 under this title, winning the 1991 [[Kodansha Manga Award]] in the General category.<ref name="KodanshaHahn">{{cite web|url=http://www.hahnlibrary.net/comics/awards/kodansha.shtml |author=Joel Hahn |title=Kodansha Manga Awards |work=Comic Book Awards Almanac |accessdate=2007-12-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071121042032/http://www.hahnlibrary.net/comics/awards/kodansha.shtml |archivedate=2007-11-21 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> As of 2013, the series has sold over 40 million copies in Japan.<ref name=83debut>{{cite web | url=http://mantan-web.jp/2013/07/11/20130710dog00m200067000c.html | script-title=ja:島耕作 ： 社長退任で「会長編」へ 連載30年節目に | date=July 11, 2013 |work=Mainichi Shimbun Digital | language=Japanese |accessdate=September 11, 2016}}</ref>
It depicts the life of a [[salaryman]], a Japanese [[white-collar worker]] who devotes his life to his company. The manga has also been published as 7 bilingual volumes (Japanese-English) called ''Division Chief Kosaku Shima''<ref>https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/541567.Division_Chief_Kosaku_Shima_Kodansha_Bilingual_Comics_Volume_5</ref> and ''President Kosaku Shima'',<ref>https://www.amazon.com/President-Kosaku-Bilingual-English-Japanese/dp/4770041322/ref=sr_1_2?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1490637923&sr=1-2&keywords=President+Kosaku+Shima</ref> and in French and German. In addition to various manga there has also been one comedic ONA, and two comedic anime adaptations lasting 11 episodes each, a live action film, and a single episode TV drama. The character also acts as the "host" or framing device for a business documentary series on [[NHK World]], ''Shima Kosaku's Asian Entrepreneurs''.
At the start of the long-running series, Shima Kōsaku is a ''kachō'', or section chief, of a huge conglomerate, Hatsushiba Electric. He is later promoted to ''buchō'' (division chief) and eventually promoted to manager and executive-director, and with each promotion the title of the series changed as well. He was promoted to the president of Hatsushiba Electric, and the title changed to "Shachō" Shima Kōsaku, which means "President Kōsaku Shima". The fictional conglomerate is modeled after [[Panasonic]], or Matsushita Electric, where Hirokane worked before and is highly accurate in its portrayal of Japanese corporate culture.
