{{Nihongo|'''Sōdanyaku'''|相談役||lit. "official advisor"}} is a [[corporate title|title]] given to senior members of [[Japan]]ese companies and non-profit organizations. A sodanyaku is often a former [[President (corporate title)|president]] or [[chairman]] of the organization who has relinquished day-to-day control of the organization but continues to offer advice to its full-time [[Management|managers]]. An advisor may be, but is not always, a [[Board of directors|director]] of the organization. Similar titles include {{Nihongo|'''chief consultant'''|最高顧問|saikō komon}} and {{Nihongo|'''advisor emeritus'''|名誉相談役|meiyo sōdanyaku}}.

